subSubSection.paragraph:
Cephalic vesicle present, slightly assymetrical, dorsal side usually longer than ventral side. In apical view, oval-shaped buccal opening surrounded by small ring; absence of interno-labial papillae, presence of four externo-labial papillae, four cephalic papillae and two amphids. Dorsal oesophageal gland very clear in apical and lateral views (
Fig. 3A, B
).

